Icons

Icon size refers to the bounding box. Actual icon size is 4px (padding) less.

Size: Medium: 24px
Size: Small: 16px
Still to do:
  • @ symbol

Deprecated Icons

These icons have gone the way of the dodo. Or dinosaurs...

Use

Figma
  • Figma file
  • Use fill not stroke and flatten shapes as much as possible.
  • Assign variable --color-text-page to the fill
  • Add in Component as variant. 24px and 16px. 2px padding around icon shapes.
  • Copy as SVG to a file.

In Code

How to use

In Astro

<Icon 
  class="sh-atom-icon" 
  icon="icon-trashcan"/>

In pimcore Twig files

{% include 'Components/Atoms/atom-icon/_atom-icon.html.twig' with {'iconName' : 'icon-trashcan'} %}

with props

Optional props: width, height, vueConditional

{% include 'Components/Atoms/atom-icon/_atom-icon.html.twig' with {'iconName' : 'icon-trashcan', 'width' : '16' } %}
